# WORKFLOW RULES

## Start of every session
1. Read the current task from CURRENT_TASK.md
2. Read relevant service files before changing anything
3. Confirm understanding of task scope before writing code
4. Do not start coding until scope is agreed

## Task states
- READY → actively working on it
- IN_PROGRESS → code written, needs test
- NEEDS_TEST → stop coding, verify behavior
- DONE → committed and working

## When to stop coding
- When a slice is written and needs testing → STOP. Do not add more.
- When you are about to touch a second service → STOP. Confirm scope.
- When you are unsure if something exists → STOP. Read the file first.

## Commit flow
1. Write code for one slice
2. Read back changes with me
3. Stage only relevant files
4. Write clean commit message
5. Push when verified